title: EastEnders' bus crash causes carnage in Albert Square — but who died?
text:
KILLER CRASH: The bus ploughed into the busy street 
bbc CARNAGE: There were several characters in the bus' way Eastenders most memorable moments Monday, 18th April 2016 From Wellard's tearjerking death to who shot Phil, here are the most memorable and shocking moments from Albert Square over the years. 1 / 25 Eastenders most shocking moments 
But who made it out alive? 
Shakil Kazemi, Louise Mitchell, Bex Fowler, Keegan and Denise are probably in the most danger as they were all in the bus. 
Will they manage to escape in time? 
Carmel Kazemi, Martin Fowler and Donna Hubbard were all in the market, desperately trying to get out of the way. 
bbc DRAMA: The bus driver had a heart attack 
bbc DANGER: The teenagers were on the top deck “Trying to make up for the shambolic Xmas episode” EastEnders viewer 
We do know that Phil and Sharon Mitchell, Jay Brown, Mick Carter, Aunt Babe, Tina and Sylvie Carter, Ian Beale and Michelle Fowler have all survived because they will appear in upcoming storylines. 
But it's unclear for now who got out of the crash safely and viewers will have to wait and see if someone gets killed off. 
Viewers had mixed responses to the crash, with one tweeting: "That bus crash was far too random. The writers were trying to make up for the shambolic Xmas and NYD episodes." 
bbc SURVIVED? Denise was right at the front of the bus The most dramatic Eastenders exits Thursday, 19th May 2016 With soap legend Peggy Mitchell leaving Eastenders for good, we take a look back at the most dramatic exits from the series 1 / 18 BBC Peggy took an overdose after her cancer returned 
"I think Donna could be one of the victims in this week's bus crash. She did say her wheelchair wasn't working," another posted. 
A third said: "A good few people better be dead & some better be seriously injured after this crash otherwise what's the point in doing it." 
While a third disagreed: "EastEnders always pull it out of the bag! Two deaths in one and now a bus crash into the market... well done BBC, well done." 
EastEnders continues tonight at 7:30pm on BBC One. Related articles
